---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
const title = `About — ${SITE.name}`;
const description = 'What Texas AI Report is, who publishes it, and how it is funded.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="col" style="padding-top:40px;padding-bottom:48px">
    <div class="kicker">About</div>
    <h1 style="margin:8px 0 24px;color:var(--navy)">About Texas AI Report</h1>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-bottom:8px">What we are</h2>
    <p>
      Texas AI Report is an independent news publication covering artificial
      intelligence policy, business, and risk in Texas. Our reporting focuses on
      how AI regulation, government adoption, and commercial deployment affect
      individuals, companies, and institutions across the state — and how Texas
      fits into the broader national and global AI governance landscape.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Mission</h2>
    <p>
      We believe AI policy is too consequential to be explained badly. Our mission
      is to provide accurate, independently sourced reporting and analysis for
      business leaders, policy practitioners, and informed Texans who need to
      understand what is actually happening — not what the press release says.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Publisher &amp; Editor</h2>
    <p>
      Texas AI Report is owned and operated by <a href="/authors/matt-bertram">Matt Bertram</a>,
      an AI-governance practitioner based in Houston, Texas. Matt is a
      NIST AI Safety Institute Consortium (AISI) participant, holds the IAPP AI
      Governance Professional (AIGP) credential, and is the holder of two
      provisional patents in AI governance. He is the founder of
      <a href="https://ewrdigital.com/">EWR Digital</a> (a digital marketing and
      technology agency) and leads <a href="https://modalpoint.com/">ModalPoint</a>
      (an AI-governance advisory).
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Funding &amp; Independence</h2>
    <p>
      At launch, Texas AI Report is self-funded. It is affiliated with EWR
      Digital and ModalPoint through common ownership. There are currently no
      paid advertisers or sponsors. Coverage decisions are made editorially and
      are independent of ModalPoint's or EWR Digital's commercial interests.
      When a story references an affiliated entity, that relationship is disclosed
      inline. See our full <a href="/disclosure">Ownership &amp; Disclosure</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Contact</h2>
    <p>
      General inquiries and editorial feedback:
      <a href="mailto:editor@texasaireport.com">editor@texasaireport.com</a><br/>
      News tips: <a href="mailto:tips@texasaireport.com">tips@texasaireport.com</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
